summary: In the game, there’s a scene at the beginning where DP is trying to see if people can understand what he’s saying as they walk...
body:
In the game, there’s a scene at the beginning where DP is trying to see if people can understand what he’s saying as they walk by.

He almost gets hit by a car and (probably) yells profanity at the driver

But this scene in the movie is so much worse because he’s probably trying to do the same thing - to see if someone understands him - but they just ignore him or some jerk drives by and splashes a puddle at him or something. It’s worse in the movie because now he’s just sad and crying and I just want to hug him ~

summary:
Detective pikachu is totally gonna be Henry. (Whatever the dad’s name is, DP is the dad)
Anyone who’s played the Pokémon dungeon...
body:
Detective pikachu is totally gonna be Henry. (Whatever the dad’s name is, DP is the dad)

Anyone who’s played the Pokémon dungeon games known that when a Pokémon has amnesia, and there’s a human somehow involved, it’s bc the human got transformed. He’s a detective (obvi), so if he came across some unethical and highly illegal Pokémon experiments that need him wacked, why not just turn him into a Pokémon? After all, who ever heard of a talking Pokémon? Everyone knows dead men tell no tales, but neither do Pokémon. (Or so they think)

I also think the flareon in the new trailer might be a recently transformed person bc those blue eyes… they just don’t look right for a flareon. Black or brown, sure. But electric blue? That’s some kind of sorcery (science) right there! That or maybe mew bc mewtwo was in it too. Why not?

Regardless, I’m so excited!!!!!
